//install angular cli
npm install -g @angular/cli









**************************
//When you use npm install -g on any platform and you get EACCES, you are writing to a 
//directory for which you do not have write permission.
//follow the next steps
Try using this: On the command line, in your home directory, create a directory for global installations:
mkdir ~/.npm-global

Configure npm to use the new directory path:
npm config set prefix '~/.npm-global'

In your preferred text editor, open or create a ~/.profile file and add this line:
export PATH=~/.npm-global/bin:$PATH

On the command line, update your system variables:
source ~/.profile

grant permission to my user
chown -R ebastreghi client-room/
*****************************





